title: For Sale:  World War II M1 Garand Carefully Refinished MUST SEE
postcontent:
This is a beautiful Cal .30 M1, manufactured during World War II at the Springfield Armory and obviously used during WWII. I purchased it from an aging WWII veteran a number of years ago and when I took it all apart I realized I had a real treasure. Obviously manufactured at the Springfield Armory at some point during WWII it must have been serviced at an arsenal depot on one of the war theaters, for it has a Winchester trigger group and HRA bolt, to my knoweldge, WWII parts.

I sent it off to Dean's Gun restoration and had the wood replaced with a beautifully well reproduction WWII stock in period stain color. It was completely reparkerized, every single part broken down and refinished, all springs replaced. 

It is a great shooter. I'm selling it because the tax man cometh in force this year.

If you are looking for a genuine piece of World War II history, this M1 Garand is for you. It is truly a collector's piece, would be a real treasure of a gift for an aging WWII veteran or to add to your collection.

I'm selling it with a reproduction WWII era soft case and reproduction leather sling.

The Muzzle wear is  minimal, around a 2.5 I'd guess, and the throat is in good shape. Unfortunately, I do not have the tools to give you a more precise measurement.

I have put only around three clips of ammo through it and it functions flawlessly.

You simply will NOT find Garands today in this kind of great condition and completely restored to their wartime, from-the-factory glory.

SERIOUS INQUIRIES ONLY.

I have a LOT more photos I can provide, just let me know.

In the STL area? FTF only at neutral location, Bob Evans at 141/44 at a mutually agreed upon time. I will not travel anywhere else to sell the rifle.

NO TRADES. Not interested, so don't ask.

Out of state? No problem. $45 for professional packaging and shipping. If you are a C&R holder, I can, of course, ship directly to you, just need a copy of your C&R License. Otherwise, I will ship to your FFL dealer. You are responsible for having your FFL dealer provide a copy of his FFL license, etc. 

Contact me BY TEXT at REDACTED. Please do not call, text only.

Or e-mail me at REDACTED

Thanks for looking!

title: For Sale:  TriStar Cobra Force Spring Loaded Pump Shotgun New in Box
postcontent:
TriStar’s Cobra Force shotgun is a Turkish-made 12-gauge tactical pump-action...New in box, unfired. 
I like face to face cash transactions with legal buyers.  I prefer not to ship.

The matte-black gun has a 20-inch cylinder-bore barrel and full stock with a pistol grip. It is chambered for 2 3/4-inch and 3-inch shotshells.  

Most noteworthy among the Cobra Force’s features is that the fore-end is mounted on a return spring. Once the gun is fired, the fore-end can be pulled rearward, compressing the spring and ejecting the hull. The fore-end is then slid forward with a considerable assist from the spring as the action chambers a fresh round. In fact, if the fore-end is released at its rearmost point, there is sufficient spring pressure to drive it forward, chambering a round and locking the action into battery. 

The virtue of the system is said to be improved speed. Additionally, it is claimed that because less force is necessary to slide the fore-end forward, accuracy is enhanced. 

The spring is easily removed if desired. Take it out and the Cobra Force functions like any other tactical pump shotgun. 

The big, hand-filling grip is covered with soft rubber, providing both secure purchase and pleasant cushioning.

title: For Sale:  Dan Wesson CBOB 1911 + 3 Mags + Kramer IWB #3 Holster
postcontent:
For sale or trade, Dan Wesson Commander Classic Bobtail 1911 + 3 Mags (2 Wilson Combat 8rds, 1 Colt 7 rd) + Kramer IWB Holster #3 Horsehide. As far as I know, these are very hard to come by now.

http://cz-usa.com/products/view/dan-wesson-commander-classic-bobtail/

$1250 , TRADES : 9mm Handguns , Straight trade or gun + cash.

http://www.kramerleather.com/productDetail.cfm?productID=7&categoryID=23

I got this gun a while back from a family member. It was his ccw weapon. When he gave it to me, he told me is has seen 1000 rounds or so. It has sat well oiled in a safe ever since he moved and hasn't seen action. I personally have never took it to the range, so I honestly can't comment on its functionality. It is a Dan Wesson though, and I've only really heard great things about them. I would take it to the range, but .45 is out of budget. I am used to my glock and don't see a reason to change. It's honestly too heavy for me . I'm too used to polymer.

The gun's finish is great considering it was carried everyday. The top of the gun is bead blasted and does have wear, it really isn't noticeable unless you rotate it under the light. The flats of the gun is a polished metal and there are blemishes on the frame where the slide release is (The scratches are really only seen when the slide release is removed). There is a light 'idiot' mark on the gun. Honestly these cosmetic flaws won't bother you unless you're buying the gun to camp in your safe. If you're looking for a gun to shoot and carry everyday, you won't mind any of it. The trigger breaks very clean. Gun features of course a bobtail as well as an aggressive front strap checkering. The Kramer holster is incredibly comfortable, and glove fit for the gun. The horsehide translates into a a rigid holster that won't lose shape like regular leather. The sights were changed to an XS Express 24/7 Big Dot, old sights included. Mainspring housing Backstrap is an ed brown part, i'm sure it isn't the only one.

I have included pictures highlighting the blemishes as best as I could. Some of the scratches are hard to see in person.
